commentPostTextItems.html: 255 was never a good looking total against this packed World XI team but the bowlers did their job exceptionally well, everyone chipped it with wickets and in the end it was a fantastic victory for the Australians
McGrath and Lee did the damage early , Bracken and Watson followed up well and one after the other the World XI batsmen were dismissed cheaply.
Watson picked up three wickets, Lee and McGrath got two each, Symonds and Bracken chipped in with one each
Pollock - I though 255 was gettable, few soft dismissals turned it the other way, We got to put it together, haven't got too many days, I am looking forward to the next one.

Ponting - `we played quite different today, we got out and played good cricket, full credit to the boys - wicket looked good and we wanted to put in a big total, 255 was always going to be a hard target, the boys bowled beautifully

milestones.description: Brian Lara has broken the record for most catches (2) in ODIs for ICC, going past Fleming's 1
Sehwag and Sangakkara's 18-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 1 between Gilchrist and Chris Gayle
Pietersen and Sangakkara's 7-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 1 between Chris Cairns and Glenn McGrath
Flintoff and Vettori's 32-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Shane Warne and Vettori
Brian Lara has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2) for ICC, going past Chris Cairns
Brian Lara has broken the record for most catches in an innings (2) in ODIs for ICC, going past Fleming's 1
Flintoff has conceded the most runs in an innings (66) in ODIs for ICC, going past Vettori's record of 58
